#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:5
msgid "Creating a Database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:7
msgid ""
"This guide shows how to create a new database, the demo (inventory-"
"system-demos/base folder) in the addon already contains a database used "
"in fps-demo. Database is a resource that will manage project-level "
"information about items, recipes, and craft stations. It contains lists "
"of internal resources for each data type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:11
msgid ""
"You can edit it via Godot's own inspector, but we recommend using the "
"plugin's own editor for this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:14
msgid "Go to **Inventory** in top view of godot editor"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:19
msgid ""
"If the Inventory tab above does not appear, it means that your plugin was"
" not installed correctly or that it was not active in the Project "
"Settings, check the :ref:`installation`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:22
msgid ""
"In this part you will see the editor empty, we will add the key file for "
"adding any resource to the inventory system, the Inventory Database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:26
msgid ""
"Select the new database option to open the window to create a new "
"database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:30
msgid ""
"Choose the name of your database and Select **Ok**(Normally a simple "
"project will have no more than one database, that is, a name like "
"'database' would already be suggested)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getting_started/quickstart/create_database.rst:34
msgid ""
"Now we can see that the editor screen has changed, showing 4 icons "
"available in the editor, to add a new item, recipe, craft-station and "
"category respectively."
msgstr ""

